The Zamfara State Police Command has asked indigenes of the State who sat for the recently conducted Computer Based Test (CBT) to report for medical screening exercise scheduled to commence from 17th May to 31st May 2022, at the 17 Police Zonal Command Headquarters nationwide. According to the State Commissioner of Police, Mr. Ayuba Elkanah, candidates from Zamfara are advised to check their application status and print out their medical screening slip to know if they qualified for the next stage of the recruitment screening exercise and the date indicated against their names. The Commissioner noted that the centre of the medical screening will be at the zone 10 Police headquarters in Sokoto State. “All applicants are to appear at the screening venue in their clean white T-shirts and shorts with the following mandatory basic requirements: “Original and duplicate copies of credentials – O’ Level Result(s), Certificate of Origin and Birth Certificate/Declaration of Age – neatly arranged in two white flat files with recent passport photographs attached” “Duly completed guarantor’s form. Any candidate who fails to present any of the above requirements will not be allowed for the screening,” he said. The Commissioner congratulated the successful candidates and reminded them that the recruitment exercise was absolutely free of charge and without any pecuniary obligation. He assured that the exercise would be carried out in accordance with the best tradition of transparency and accountability, and called on them to be wary of online imposters and other criminal elements who might want to take advantage of the exercise to dupe innocent applicants.